    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">PESCO Reference Number — Where is it on Your Bill?</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">The PESCO reference number is a 14-digit number on the top-right of your electricity bill. You need this number to check your PESCO bill online or make payments through JazzCash, EasyPaisa, or any bank app.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Where is the reference number on PESCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The PESCO reference number is on the top-right section of your bill, labeled Ref. No. or Reference No. It is a 14-digit number printed in bold, directly above the barcode on the bill.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the PESCO reference number format?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The PESCO reference number is always 14 digits. No letters, no dashes. Example: 01234567890123. It stays the same every month and is used for all online payments and bill checking.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check PESCO bill without reference number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Use your 10-digit PESCO Customer ID instead — it also works on our checker. Or call PESCO helpline 118 with your CNIC and address to get your reference number.</div></details>
    </div>

